rComments: He is actually a good professor
Peter Herman is a world-class scholar, a brilliant man and an unparalleled writer. I'm lucky to have had this class; it's a wonder to have a course led by a luminary in their field. Take him.

He is always late for lectures, and he sometimes forgets to bring his lecture notes. Sometimes, he comes back to the lecture room after searching for his notes, "I lost my notes!". He confuses whatever you've learned so far. If you have him, you MUST avoid his lectures at all cost, even your balls.

This man is very intelligent. I loved coming to class just to listen to him speak; his sense of humour here and there also made the lectures more enjoyable. Although his test questions weren't always fair and I didn't do too well, I loved this course!
This guy is just there to collect a paycheck, he doesn't care about the students and he shows up late to his own tests.
Inspiring prof. There needs to be more Professors like Herman.
If you listen carefully enough, you'll find that he actually has a wicked sense of humour! Plus, he knows what he's talking about. Now if he could only work on that personality of his...
Good sense of (dry) humour. Very cynical yet very warm and caring when it comes to his students.
